headline.main: IMPORTANT FROM NICARAGUA.; DISTURBANCES AT CHONTALES. THE COURT-MARTIAL ON SOHLES SINGER. WALKER FIRMLY ESTABLISHED. RIVAS RE-ELECTED PRESIDENT. PROBABLE END OF THE WAR. Particulars of the Costa Rican Retreat ARRVIAL OF THE ORIZABI. RAVAGES OF CHOLERA IN THEIR RAWKE. THE TRANSIT ROUTE AGAIN OPEN.

docs.lead_paragraph: The steamship Oruoba, Capt. E. L. TINKLE. PAUOH, arrived yeserday from San Juan del Norto with 156 passengers, most of whom left San Frauciaco May 5 on the Surra Nevada. The Tranoite mouto through Niearagun is again open, the Costa Ricans haveing left the country without anothor battie.
